A vintage-style travel photograph of Hanoi, Vietnam in warm sepia and amber tones, featuring the iconic red-painted Long Bien Bridge spanning across the Red River at golden hour. In the foreground, traditional wooden boats with curved prows float on calm waters reflecting the sunset sky. Industrial smokestacks rise in the misty background, their plumes catching the evening light, symbolizing the meeting of tradition and industry. The composition has the grainy, slightly faded quality of 1960s travel photography, with rich earth tones and soft vignetting around the edges. Palm trees and bamboo frame the scene, while the distant silhouette of the city emerges through atmospheric haze.
